Family owned and operated. The owners have been in the restaurant business for over 25 years, so they know how to pick quality meat, seafood and chicken. The food tastes authentic to it's culture. There is a bar and large dining area for larger seating or a smaller section for a more intimate experience. The margaritas are delicious! They have Modelo, Heinkein and of course Corona at the bar. They have most rail and top shelf liquors too. Highly recommend this restaurant if you want a homemade meal away from home.

They immediately assume you want bottled water and charged us at the end for it without saying a word.  Worst of all they charged group gratuity of 18% for a party of 4, WHO DOES THAT?? Checking out took 20 minutes in a nearly empty restaurant, the staff put us completely away from other guests, and after asking to itemize our list of food so we could split it up, she just pretended to not understand and did it 50/50.  This place is a scam.

This place was amazing and everything we were looking for. I felt it when I walked in the door, "authenticity" from the welcoming hosts, the smiling guests, the decor, the music...and then the food blew me away. My husband is from LA and wanted me to get a feel of what to expect when we move there next month and OMG....I wanted to grab a waitress and dance!!! We ordered the chicken enchiladas and a beef burrito and they were both like fireworks to my taste buds. My favorite...the burrito hands down!! Im so excited to try something else from the menu tonight!!! Lol needless to say I highly recommend this place!!
